article.description: Omar Prewitt poured in 21 points and 10 of his 11 teammates scored as William & Mary ran away from Division III Mary Washington in the second half Friday night.
article.headline: William & Mary roar past Mary Washington in 2nd half, 94-64
article.linkText: William & Mary roar past Mary Washington in 2nd half, 94-64
article.story: WILLIAMSBURG, Va. -- Omar Prewitt poured in 21 points and 10 of his 11 teammates scored as William & Mary ran away from Division III Mary Washington in the second half Friday night. Mary Washington took a 40-33 into intermission and pushed the lead to nine on John Lutkenhaus' layup to start the second half. But Greg Malinowski answered with back-to-back 3-pointers to spark a 15-0 run that included a Prewitt trey that gave the Tribe a 48-42 lead. William & Mary went on a 16-0 run midway through the second half to take a 73-48 advantage and outscored the Eagles 61-24 over the final 20 minutes. Daniel Dixon scored 17 points and Malinowski added 15 for the Tribe (6-3). Lutkenhaus, who hit 5 of 11 from beyond the 3-point arc, finished with 23 points to lead Mary Washington, with Tj Jones adding another 11.
